  <title>SET DIGITS Command</title>
  <keywords>
    <keyword>Commands</keyword>
    <keyword>Decimals<keyword>setting number of digits</keyword></keyword>
    <keyword>Digits<keyword>setting decimals</keyword></keyword>
    <keyword>Displaying<keyword>numbers</keyword></keyword>
    <keyword>Environment</keyword>
    <keyword>SET DIGITS command</keyword>
  </keywords>
  <body>
    <header>
      <para styleclass="Heading1">SET DIGITS Command</para>
    </header>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><snippet src="__CommandInclude" inline="false"/></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Heading1">Purpose</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal">Change the setting that determines the number of digits that will be shown to the left of the decimal point when a number is displayed.</para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Heading1">Syntax</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal">SET DIGITS TO [&lt;<text styleclass="Italic">nDigits</text>&gt;]</para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Heading1">Description</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal">SET DIGITS is functionally equivalent to SetDigit(). &#160;</para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"></para>
    <para styleclass="Body Text"><snippet src="__IncludeLibRT" inline="false"/></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Heading1">See Also</text></para>
